 Blurb?..[Y].....................................:  Program for calculating traveltimes for
 focal depths and distances uses a set of
 tau-p tables for the XXXX model stored as
  xxxx.hed and xxxx.tbl -- e.g.  iasp91
 At the prompt for v-z model path, enter the path.
   e.g., ../build-tables/iasp91

 v-z model path..................................:  Enter phase codes or keywords for desired branches
 Terminate the list with a carriage return
 ALL gives all available branches
 P  gives P-up,P,Pdiff,PKP, and PKiKP
 P+ gives P-up,P,Pdiff,PKP,PKiKP,PcP,pP,pPdiff,pPKP,
          pPKiKP,sP,sPdiff,sPKP, and sPKiKP
 S  gives S-up,S,Sdiff, and SKS
 S+ gives S-up,S,Sdiff,SKS,sS,sSdiff,sSKS,pS,pSdiff,
          and pSKS 
 basic gives P+ and S+ as well as 
          ScP, SKP, PKKP, SKKP, PP, and PKPPKP 
 Or can just give generic phase name(s)

 phase_code=P       
 Enter desired branch control list at the prompts:
** Brnset:  the following phases have been selected -
              1  P       
              2  PKP       P       
              3  PKiKP   
              4  pPKP      pP      
              5  sPKP      sP      
              6  pPKiKP  
              7  sPKiKP  
              8  PcP     
              9  ScP     
             10  SKP     
             12  PKKP    
             13  SKKP    
             14  P'P'      PP      
             15  S       
             16  SKS       S       
 Epicent. distances may be in deg. or km
 Will you use kilometers? (Y or N) ..[N].........:  Prompts for focal depth & epicentral distance
 A negative depth terminates the program
 A negative distance => prompt for new depth

Source depth_min,depth_max,depth_step (km):  
 depth_min,depth_max,depth_step =  0.000  80.000   1.000

 You will have to enter a distance,
 if this is negative a new depth is calculated
 TO EXIT: give negative depth


Enter delta_min,delta_max,delta_step:  
 delta_min,delta_max,delta_step =   0.00   20.00    0.01
  delta   times------------

